7DK3QVMBY3QMGLHA','E. Britton','the United States','May 5, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AE5J6OTQO54N7DK3QVMBY3QMGLHA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  After looking for weeks for a good gaming laptop with somewhat future proof internals for under 1500 this Laptop finally popped up. It looks nice has a great screen and is lightning fast.Pros:Great 144hz ScreenNew i7 and Full RTX2070Its got a pretty keyboardCons: Fans can be very loudSome bloatware installed\n\n','positive','subjective',0.773,1,'2020-07-31 00:43:01.810599'),(66,220,'AHTXXAA6BHMMQ7PNVT63WNIOVUHQ','T Greene','the United States','May 14, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHTXXAA6BHMMQ7PNVT63WNIOVUHQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I\'ve ALWAYS had Macs and have never considered PC\'s till my Macbook died. I then bought an HP with better specs than this laptop, and am returning the HP because this MSI laptop is just that much better. I\'ve only had this laptop for 2 weeks and so far it\'s worth every penny. I don\'t use it for gaming but the CPU speed is amazing, everything is quick. I use Ableton for Music Production and require a laptop that can process tons of different moving parts at the same time. Ableton is running better than ever on this, I haven\'t had any CPU crashes or overloads whatsoever. The only reason this isn\'t the perfect laptop for me is the speaker. The laptop\'s speaker quality is very mediocre. Granted, the laptop audio quality is stellar. When plugged into headphones or other speakers, it sounds great. I just wish the speakers on the laptop gave a better quality sound. Nonetheless, it\'s worth it.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.79,1,'2020-07-31 00:43:01.812621'),(67,220,'AGFXUP6SIHMS7KIPHFH34SN2SGHQ','Malak AS','the United States','April 29, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGFXUP6SIHMS7KIPHFH34SN2SGHQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  when you want to buy a laptop i have the one for you, it\'s not that expensive and it\'s amazing. You\'ll have everything you need in this laptop. Pros: It\'s the best, Cons: There\'s no cons.BUY IT IF YOU CAN.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.664,1,'2020-07-31 00:43:01.822781'),(68,220,'AEZES5A7E454ZPAKIE5HSXQL3V6Q','Diggums','the United States','May 1, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEZES5A7E454ZPAKIE5HSXQL3V6Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  So right out of the box, this laptop is very sturdy and well made! It feels like a black aluminum casing. The fans have been pretty quiet thus far. Running Final Fantasy 14 on max graphics in an over populated zone and it is holding up extremely well! Even the MSI Dragon software works pretty well for monitoring the Laptop\'s performance! Super happy with this purchase so far! Can\'t wait to really put it to the test!\n\n','positive','subjective',0.527,1,'2020-07-31 00:43:01.832128'),(69,221,'AFJYN5DB66CRGURVJSPBDLV3LOFA','Spiral','the United States','October 21, 2018',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFJYN5DB66CRGURVJSPBDLV3LOFA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I’ve tried the rest:J+S Vision Blue Light Shield  $28.99Pro: Inexpensive, light, comfortable on face, no magnification.Con:Right eye pain, yellow tint detracts from colors on screen and might be the cause of slight eye pain in both eyes.GAMEKING Ultra G603 $39.99Pro: Inexpensive, very light,comfortable on face.Con: Yellow tint detracts from colors on screen with slight magnification might be the cause of right eye pain.Gunnar Optiks Valve $69.99Pro: Light weight,nice looking.Con: Yellow tint detracts from colors on screen with slight magnification might be the cause of right eye pain....Now i’ve tried, what i believe to be the best.Hyper X $99.99Pro: Video on Amazon product page shows blue light being reflected from lens, meaning the blue light does not penetrate the lens. Light weight. Clear lens. No eye pain in either eye.Con: Expensive, frame is small, no lens cleaner wipe,under belly of frame is red, tend to slide down nose, will need to purchase frame strap to reduce frames from sliding, no nose hinges.These are the 1st edition, i may give these to a family member when version 2.0 is released. Hope they read these cons and fix them in the next edition. I noticed Amazons availability of these glasses go from 15 to 0 with my purchase reducing this number but i don’t see corresponding reviews with these purchases. I hope more buyers review this item in the future. Hope this pro and con list helps someone. Any questions, please feel free to post on this page and i will do my best to respond.Update: glasses seem to work as intended, short sessions of gaming or longer then usual hours in front of television no longer result in headaches. However, after extended wearing, i noticed that these galsses tend to put a lot of pressure on the bridge of the nose which results in pain and very indented red marks. Also, i needed to pick up from rei a pair of the around the neck lens holders as the glassess tend to slip down the nose as well. I would still recommend these glasses though.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.744,1,'2020-07-31 00:44:53.312216'),(70,221,'AEWMC4YMTYSHVSSXLT5URMOQ3IJQ','David K.','the United States','August 3, 2017',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEWMC4YMTYSHVSSXLT5URMOQ3IJQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  So...since these just came out of the market, I knew I should write a review. I work behind my desk for a living and when I get home, 80% of the time you can find me on pc or console. I saw these glasses at their Dreamhack Atlanta booth and was curious to know if they would help my eye strain. I wished I remember who I talked too, she was incredible and informative, but she straight up said you\'re not going to notice a difference right away but if you\'re behind a screen for more than 40 hours a week you\'ll notice it. She was right. Since I\'ve been back from Dreamhack, my eyes were completely shot for the week until these came in the mail. I was skeptical at first, but the really do make a difference. Im able to knock out reports and stay focused on the screen for much longer now. At the end of the day, my eyes feel hydrated and I can keep them open. Buy a pair if you\'re eyes are strained or youre getting headaches. You wont regret it. I attached a picture showing how they handle fluorescent lights in my office. Crazy!\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.408,1,'2020-07-31 00:44:53.320195'),(71,221,'AHSTB5N4NTOUQKICZ7KHWDCYNFEA','Mike','the United States','October 23, 2017',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHSTB5N4NTOUQKICZ7KHWDCYNFEA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n   Great glasses. Seriously. Eye strain is something I’ve experienced after long days of work and game.  By the end of the night my eyes are exhausted, dry, and I’ve frequently left the end of the night with headaches. After using the eyewear, I did see improvement on how I felt at the end of the night. Anything that can improve the longevity I am able to game and work effectively I will buy into. After using the glasses for a week straight, the biggest positive is how comfortable they are. I work in front of a computer display my entire day. 8 hours during a day job, another 6-8 as a gamer. I’ve not worn glasses since I was a young kid, to say that I’m not used to wearing something on my face the whole day is an understatement.Pros:-Extremely comfortable.-High quality frames, not lame plastic.-Stands up to blue light test. Does prevent substantial amount of blue light from passing through lens.Cons:-Spring hinges on the arms of the glasses made it so the frames didn\'t hug my head as tightly as I would have liked. Still very happy with how comfortable these are however.I’d give it the thorough look if you’re in the technology field or find yourself just more than the average gamer. Stamp of approval. Highly recommend.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.791,1,'2020-07-31 00:44:53.324184'),(72,221,'AFO73VYNPYDCGE6DB2EAR2LVNW2Q','Alatariel','the United States','August 7, 2018',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFO73VYNPYDCGE6DB2EAR2LVNW2Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I’ve been waiting to review the glasses until I’ve worn them for some time. I’ve had them for the better part of a few weeks now, so I will give my take on them.First I’ll start off by saying I have 20/20 vision and do not normally wear glasses. I am a graphic designer so I spend a good 40 hours a week in front of a screen. I also like to play video games, so that adds more screen time. As of now, I use them mainly for work. The first two days of wearing them took some time to adjust to having a pair of frames on my face for 8hr a day. After that, I got use to wearing them and they didn’t irritate me as much.During the short time that I have used them (just a few weeks) I have noticed my eyes are not as dry and irritated (if at all) after work. The blue light filter seems to be working in the way intended. I like this pair in that they do not have a yellow tint to them, like many other “gaming” glasses I have seen. This helps when you are dealing with my line of work and need to have colors be spot on.They are very stylish in design and the hard case and protective sleeve that come with the glasses are an extra plus. I can carry them in my purse without worry of scratching and use them anywhere I need.The only downside I have to these is that they are a bit bigger on my face and tend to slide off my nose. The frame is one solid piece, so there is no way to adjust the nose part to stay. A smaller framed pair might help with that, but these only come in one size. For the price, I would have hoped they fit properly, but as they came from online and not a physical glasses store, that is harder to achieve.\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.454,1,'2020-07-31 00:44:53.329171'),(73,83,'AF54A6KJTX77BF2WDBJTFBJ2VKRQ','GUY','the United States','July 17, 2020',1,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AF54A6KJTX77BF2WDBJTFBJ2VKRQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  After spending nearly $1000.00 for this laptop, hours on the phone, and days trying to apply the pages and pages of instructional fixes  sent by email from ASUS,  I called  Amazon  Tech Support, and after spending over an hour on the phone, including 30 minutes on hold while he tried to contact ASUS Tech Support, was told that he could not help me.  He told me my choices were to try again later or return the laptop.  I asked him if I would still get a full refund and he assured me I would.  For an original cost of $974.74, I received a refund of $794.74,  The WiFi, Sound, and Camera were dissatisfactory.  with other devices all maintaining WiFi connectivity, this laptop lost continuously lost connection.  The sound quality was very poor, and when in a Zoom meeting, the picture displayed thru it\'s camera would flicker and then show only a green screen while all other zoom members\' photos were stable.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.912,1,'2020-07-31 00:45:24.182983'),(74,83,'AE73RLCVFPHGQBP5SGZ2G3B5ABEA','Osvaldo H Godina','the United States','July 8, 2020',2,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AE73RLCVFPHGQBP5SGZ2G3B5ABEA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I am unhappy with the PC. It is sometimes impossible to upload videos from my iphone to the PC. I was reading online that it might be a glitch from iOS. I have tried everything I could find online to fix the problem. After paying so much money it would be good to consistently and without issues upload my pictures and videos from my iphone to the PC. If you have an iphone it is probably best to get an Apple product. ......other than that issue it is a good computer. The keyboard is big and comfortable. The screen is not too small and easy to read. The back lit keyboard is a great feature. As far as the specs goes it works for me. I just wish the iphone and PC would sync consistently.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.697,1,'2020-07-31 00:45:24.189963'),(75,83,'AH2CAIBQEOSEJUMMSQLEAJPSXMTQ','Bethany Galovin','the United States','July 18, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AH2CAIBQEOSEJUMMSQLEAJPSXMTQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?