,83,'AEEKZ2HUSBQDR6VNOBUME7VE74YA','Agnieszka M.','the United States','June 10, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEEKZ2HUSBQDR6VNOBUME7VE74YA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Buen audio, buena pantalla (aunque es una pantalla antireflejos) . Corre programas como AutoCAD y revit super rápido. Teclado suave. Me gustó mucho. Excelente calidad precio.\n\n','positive','unknown',0.769,0,'2020-07-31 00:45:24.219886'),(80,83,'AEOLMFTC2LTV4BDTQDM3HG5YCNJA','Colorado Kuch','the United States','June 19, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEOLMFTC2LTV4BDTQDM3HG5YCNJA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Super fast.  The web camera is a little weak and flashes out, otherwise 5 stars.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.725,0.987,'2020-07-31 00:45:24.225868'),(81,246,'AGOPM4QQOHZXKSILWISA7HDAVADQ','Joe','the United States','August 1, 2017',2,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGOPM4QQOHZXKSILWISA7HDAVADQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Tablet is solid. The keyboard is about as good as it gets in this size, a little thick but that makes it easier to use if somewhat less compact. It is about as fast as you would expect with the given specs. Battery life is acceptable if not great, probably good for about 6-8 hours in mixed use, probably only about 4-5 if you are doing steady video or something like that. Unfortunately it didn\'t really work very well for very long, maybe two days. I almost immediately noticed that windows were getting minimized randomly. At first I chalked this up to maybe bumping the touchpad with my palm as I was typing or something, but it soon became apparent it was doing it entirely on it\'s own. I then noticed that I would get random \"touch\" detection in the lower right corner (Windows \"show desktop\" shortcut) which would minimize all open windows, and sometimes restore them a few seconds later. This got worse over the course of a couple days until it became unusable. Then, suddenly the problem was solved, but not in a good way. Instead of registering constant touch it would register no touch at all on the far right 1/4\" or so. Going back.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.825,1,'2020-07-31 00:51:49.425864'),(82,246,'AE5FG3THUHCU7LMGUE75H22O57TA','Mona Cabler','the United States','December 6, 2017',3,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AE5FG3THUHCU7LMGUE75H22O57TA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  It\'s ok.  I shopped around and read tons of reviews.  Ultimately I decided on this unit.  I wasn\'t really interested in the Windows OS but liked the specs for Android.  The build quality is very good and the unit seems very solid.  After 4 weeks of use, here are my pros and cons:Pros:Well BuiltSpeedy Android performanceNice screen & easy detachment / re-attachment to keyboardNice keyboard layoutEasy to disable trackpad with function keyStable Android and no issues installing and running appsLots of good connections like HDMI, USB, etc.ConsA bit heavy even without the keyboardShort battery life (3 hrs)Slow battery charge - if below 20% battery you cannot charge fast enough to use the device while charging before battery goes deadMicroSD card slot is basically un-usable - it constantly un-mounts the card and reports errors regardless of the size of the card or classCharging light is on the front of the screen bezel instead of side or back... you can\'t tell if it\'s charging when closed with keyboard attachedAlthough it is easy to disable the trackpad... which is a pain to have on as it picks up the slightest palm touch... but you have to do this every time you start the device.  Needs a setting to permanently disable.No good documentation on system setup - I wanted to remove the Windows OS but it seems risky as it may brick the systemSupport is un-responsive - sent an email and go no response from support.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.818,1,'2020-07-31 00:51:49.425864'),(83,246,'AFWOWYX7VLBJ5I73CFXWTTXBJB5A','Jason H','the United States','June 23, 2017',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFWOWYX7VLBJ5I73CFXWTTXBJB5A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I\'ve had this little machine for just a day, but I\'m in love with it. 4 GB of RAM and 64 GB hard drive are hard to find near this price.  2 GB RAM is NOT enough to run Windows 10, so I was really glad to find this device at $199 with 4 GB RAM. 64 GB hard drive perfect for a dual-boot system like this, and leaves about 25 GB of free hard drive space after installing Windows 10 updates and deleting old versions of Windows.The performance is great. Apps are snappy and quick. Screen quality is much better than I expected for a device under $200. Works great with my stylus. Keyboard is comfortable to type on, although the trackpad is very sensitive, so you can\'t touch it at all while you type or bad things happen...I think ALLDOCUBE nailed their goal with this product. $199, 4 GB RAM, 64 GB HD, WIndows 10, no junkware, 25 GB free space, fast, Android, tablet or laptop, quality touch screen, solid keyboard, USB 2 and 3, HDMI, front and back cameras. A+\n\n','positive','subjective',0.993,1,'2020-07-31 00:51:49.425864'),(84,246,'AGEFGIRT36Q6IYHT4XO2VYLAHMXA','Phil H','the United States','August 2, 2017',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGEFGIRT36Q6IYHT4XO2VYLAHMXA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  It has all the features I need but it has an annoying habit of jumping around due to a hair trigger on the control touch pad. Typing into something like FB comments becomes almost impossible as it will jump to a different place when using the keyboard. I haven\'t figured out how to overcome this yet. Other than this annoying characteristic, it would get a 5 star. Update, I was sent a new keyboard and this one is working fine so I\'ve upgraded this product to 5 stars. I can\'t rate their product support as anything but superb.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.999,1,'2020-07-31 00:51:49.441484'),(85,246,'AFNBAVDPFI6MTFOTJGAG6PTPXXBA','Amazon Customer','the United States','July 15, 2017',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFNBAVDPFI6MTFOTJGAG6PTPXXBA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Good for surfing, old games(xp era), and streaming. Definitely worth the price for the package you are getting. Android 5.1 is kinda pointless, because it takes longer to boot than windows, and it doesn\'t do as much, so besides the fact of \"oh im a tablet, now im a computer, now im a tablet computer!\", it\'s pointless. Hard drive space is slim, but manageable( if android was removed it would be a lot better). USE CHARGEING CABLE PROVIDED!!! The cable it comes with has a weird brick and is only 1ft long, but if you try to use a different, longer usb cable, it will die and have to completely recharge before it will turn back on. Let it die(ie. drain the battery) when you first get it and then fully recharge before using. Other than storage(which is expandable internally and externally via usb) and the finicky battery, this product is great. Awesome hardware and very well made. The track pad/ keyboard is a little touchy sometimes and will randomly minimize your window with no warning. TO USE THIS PRODUCT WITH NO ISSUE I recommend a wireless mouse, external hard drive, and maybe and extension cord for the dinky little charger provided.  Other than the little quirks it has, it is wonderful, stunning display, and will be just as good as a $600 notebook if you know how to make it work for you. Don\'t let the minor flaws deter you, because this little machine has the potential to save you a good bit of mullah.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.838,1,'2020-07-31 00:51:49.441484'),(86,247,'AFRJXMN2ONGRFYOCX2JUE4BAAVLQ','Steve McCauley','the United States','March 26, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFRJXMN2ONGRFYOCX2JUE4BAAVLQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I am fairly picky when it comes to these lap desks as I use them all the time. I have had several over the years but I have only had a few that I really liked. This one is the best one I have ever had. It was more expensive than most of the others but well worth it compared to the other junk on the 