as adhesive on it that you peel back the sticker and attach it yourself. For $50 they can even stick a nail or two in this to keep it in place?! I\'ve had this item for a week and it\'s already come off.-The slot for the phone or ipad isn\'t big enough for for even the slimmest case. This wasn\'t a selling point for me so it\'s not a dealbreaker, but still kind of annoying.The good:-The bamboo seems to be of good quality and looks nice-The cushion part is very comfortable. It molds to you which is why I chose this particular item.-The color (I chose green) is very nice.Bottom line:If they hadn\'t cheaped out at the very end and not bothered to attach the piece that keeps your laptop or book from sliding off, this would be a great product. However, that\'s an essential function for me so I\'ll be returning this item and choosing a different brand.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.705,1,'2020-07-31 00:57:53.228964'),(97,248,'AFJASIYK4Y4DSQY32IM4I4UZ664Q','Tammy ','the United States','February 5, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFJASIYK4Y4DSQY32IM4I4UZ664Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Perfect for all ages!\n\n','positive','subjective',0.807,0.916,'2020-07-31 00:57:53.233948'),(98,171,'AGZTP7DPJQRYVZ7WYENFAN7WATZA','Riley Vick','the United States','July 25, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGZTP7DPJQRYVZ7WYENFAN7WATZA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I am very pleased with the Full HD IPD screen. The picture is amazingly clear. My other favorite piece is the backlit keyboard. It lights up when you type, stays light for a little bit, then goes dark when not touched.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.962,1,'2020-07-31 00:58:47.018892'),(99,171,'AGDJUBQUYP4N3VQRRY2UZT4D5CSA','Jaspepper','the United States','July 25, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGDJUBQUYP4N3VQRRY2UZT4D5CSA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This laptop is really light, well made (aluminum, not plastic). I bought it for travelling. It seems to have a very long battery life.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.87,1,'2020-07-31 00:58:47.025872'),(100,250,'AGAXBMLYHEPXVD763OTEK4HZ5UWQ','Enigma954','the United States','July 5, 2019',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGAXBMLYHEPXVD763OTEK4HZ5UWQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I\'ve received a few laptops in my search for a gaming laptop that is also good for content creation. This laptop hits all my requirements with flying colors.It runs current titles well at ultra settings.The laptop does really well with not having noticeable screen bleed. The display is sharp and the 240 Hz refresh rate looks amazing when playing eSports titles.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.782,1,'2020-07-31 00:59:35.229298'),(101,250,'AHDP6Q3M3F6ENVD665A32NO72DTQ','Kmajed','the United States','July 8, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHDP6Q3M3F6ENVD665A32NO72DTQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This computer has all the necessary internals to be an amazing gaming computer. It runs every title extremely well. It is aesthetically pleasing, and has so many different great functions. It doesn’t get that hot when running games, keeping in mind how challenging it is for a company to keep gaming laptops cooled. The only complaint I have is the brightness of the screen seems to be lacking. Other than that you can’t go wrong with this gaming laptop.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.991,1,'2020-07-31 00:59:35.235283'),(102,250,'AGU5ADWK2JSLY7DAACHT4PGBCNFQ','Jonathan M. Hyland','the United States','August 8, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGU5ADWK2JSLY7DAACHT4PGBCNFQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This was purchased to be my primary gaming laptop. Having played both Prey and Final Fantasy XIV: Shadowbringers on Very High/Maximum settings with no frame drops (60 FPS/60 Hz monitor) at UHD resolution, the ROG Strix III Scar Edition can run the majority of modern games on the most gorgeous settings. The laptop offers a 1 TB SSD drive, giving tons of storage for your gaming library and ensuing fast start - up and gameplay.The laptop\'s built - in screen is a dream to look at and provides clear and crisp gameplay. The sound system (Realtek Audio) is sufficiently clear and powerful enough to provide an immersive sound experience. The laptop supports several external devices via 3 USB3 ports; one USB-C; HDMI; and Ethernet.\n\n','neutral','objective',0.511,1,'2020-07-31 00:59:35.239272'),(103,250,'AGGP6RXL74QPNO4EIRDM6OKHVN5Q','Sigma','the United States','April 14, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGGP6RXL74QPNO4EIRDM6OKHVN5Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  It handles any game I through at it at max settings.  Overall I\'m VERY impressed!  I upgraded it with a 2tb Seagate Firecuda SSHD and it\'s just the laptop of my dreams.  Besides the glitches with windows (no fault of Asus) it\'s perfect!  I wish I would\'ve waited just a bit longer for the RTX Supers for mobile to be released, but I\'m so happy with this purchase anyway.  I still would\'ve chosen Asus.Thermals:The fans are appropriately loud for the power that you get.  The cooling solution is very good!  I\'m incredibly impressed by the fact that it doesn\'t get hot to the touch, just warm!  Where you sit your palm stays cold!My MSI Ge62 Apache Pro 2qf had horrible thermals despite also having two fans.  This laptop does have one additional radiator, and the 2070 is more efficient than the 970m though, so that plays into the incredibly good thermal dissipation.Sturdiness:It feels premium, that sums it up.  You get what you pay for with Asus.  A $2k laptop should feel the part, and it really does!  The RGB sorta shows it too!  If you\'re a shower, this pretty much presents itself!  When you open it up, the textured aluminum deck will impress you.  That isn\'t painted or dipped, it\'s actually textured to achieve the carbon fiber look!  It\'s the little things that are getting me on this thing, as all the important things are pretty much as close to perfect as something like this could come.Sound:For a laptop of this size, sound is top notch!  Bass is incredible and It\'s hard to believe it comes out of such a small body.Display:This 240Hz IPS panel is just amazing!  It looks higher res than 1080p to me and I\'m not sure why.  I\'m coming from a TN 60Hz panel, so maybe that\'s it?  Anyway, color reproduion is great and results in a beautiful visual presentation.  The fluid motion of everything thanks to the 240Hz refresh rate is just eye candy.  Personally, I see the difference.I have also proven that this panel is truely refreshing as 240Hz.  TestUFO.com will be able to show you the difference between 60, 120, and 240 Hz.  While it doesn\'t stick out, 240Hz is noticeably better here.The only negative of this panel is the max display brightness.  It\'s a little bit hard to see in the daylight, but who will be taking their laptop outside in the middle of the day?Issues:This only issue I\'ve had are either petty, or not Asus\'s fault.-  The keystone keychain holder was torn a bit (not important at all for me)-  Updating the KB firmware was a little janky.-  RGB software is also rather janky.  It works, but doesn\'t feel \"complete.\"UPDATE (6/23/2020):Unfortunately, there is only one USB host controller for all ports.  There is no internal host controller for non-user devices.  Everything is shared on one chip.  A three camera setup for the Oculus CV1 is very difficult to get working.  Usually, two cameras will default to USB 2.0 because of bandwidth issues.  It\'s a shame this wasn\'t taken into account, but overall it\'s still a good laptop.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.993,1,'2020-07-31 00:59:35.244259'),(104,250,'AF3EG3CC7JIQEVDU6B3VX2ULFQSA','Cuong Nguyen','the United States','July 16, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AF3EG3CC7JIQEVDU6B3VX2ULFQSA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  The specs on this laptop is amazing. This is the cheapest gaming laptop with RTX 2070. The build quality is good. Conclusion: this laptop is perfect for gaming and daily use.\n\n','positive','objective',0.996,0.814,'2020-07-31 00:59:35.249245'),(105,250,'AEB2S76KCQF2OQBVBIEBUTCIQJWA','Omar','the United States','December 6, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEB2S76KCQF2OQBVBIEBUTCIQJWA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Ok, first things first, this is my first gaming pc because in the past i bought a laptop without knowing much about graphics card and stuff like that, and i wasnt great for what i wanted to do on it, with all that, its was an asus machine it lasted for 3 years, its still working but the charging port needs to be replaced, but as you know thats why i went for an asus machine for a gaming laptop because my previous laptop had a intel hd 520 and still i got some games i got to enjoy and never had a system issue, now this machine is premium to me, the way it was built, the design, the spec, this is really what i paid for and more!! to put it in perspective, i just started playing COD MW and Star Wars Jedi Fallen Order, and it goes SMOOOOTH!!! like, MW i play it on Epic and with RTX on and never had a frame dropped bellow 60 fps, and Star wars looks amazing with this screen. The \"bad\" (Just annoying to me) stuff that i could say about it is that the armoury crate is the most broken app here, it works.....when it wants, controlling RGB light is alright but if you\'re buying an asus accessorie with Aura Sync, well i just have to say \"good luck with that\" because you\'\'ll end up like me and just leaving the mouse be on its own whithout syncing it because 70% of the time it wont work, and the last \"bad thing\" would be the mouse pad, i mean, i use a mouse so i dont really care, but when im using the machine without a mouse hmmm you from time to time will enable the num pad, but i dont really mind, in 2 days of use i believe i\'ve turn it on by accident like 6 times.In conclusion if you like asus and if u like gaming well buy this, it looks great, and it performs like a dime.....PS: the fans are loud but not that loud, if you\'ve been living in silence well it could bother you but if you live in constant noise in your work or house you wont mind like me when youre used to general noise, the fans are like a lego jet or something xD\n\n','negative','subjective',0.412,1,'2020-07-31 00:59:35.255229'),(106,182,'AFQZFVDEPM3ARDOOWVM6AMJ5UMAA','kanuhobrewer','the United States','January 23, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFQZFVDEPM3ARDOOWVM6AMJ5UMAA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I went for this computer because it has an i3 processor, an SSD drive, a 15.6\" screen, comes in a beautiful darker blue color and from what I read from other reviewers, the SSD drive and RAM are both upgradeable. For $280 this is well worth the value.It\'s lightning fast, have no problem connecting to WIFI or bluetooth. The keyboard stretches from both ends, making it larger than a lot of keyboards on laptops this size as others also fit the speakers on both ends then the keyboard in between, and the keys are quiet, responsive and nicely saved.It does come in S-Mode but you can easily switch it to Windows 10 Mode. This is the first thing I did. Right after I tried watching YouTube videos to see how video streaming went and it was awful. Anytime something even just a bit fast happened, it would blur or jump frame rates. As it turns out though the fix was checking for any Windows Update and there was plenty.It took about 30 minutes altogether to update the laptop. After you check for updates, you\'ll have to restart your computer. Then, you\'ll need to check for updates again and restart your computer, again. Then do this one more time and check for updates. After your third time having to restart you shouldn\'t have any more updates. After I did this, I tried watching YouTube videos again and everything was smooth and perfect.I mainly use it for typing, browsing the Internet (have had so far up to 10 tabs open at once) and occasionally watching YouTube and Netflix. I also downloaded League of Legends and it definitely plays it well. I haven\'t made any upgrades to it yet, just because there hasn\'t been any need to but if there is eventually a need to, it\'s nice to know I will be able to and not have to buy another laptop, producing more waste and costing more money.I actually have 0 complaints. It\'s everything you expect and a bit more for a laptop in this price amazing. Having an i3, which I believe this one is 8th gen, is definitely beneficial.\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.363,1,'2020-07-31 01:00:46.935837'),(107,182,'AHS4LEDURQ2FHGB536BODUMRE2AQ','Dirtt Coyote','the United States','February 2, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHS4LEDURQ2FHGB536BODUMRE2AQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I had some doubts about this laptop at first, I thought it was going to be a real junker at under $300, but it turns out that this laptop has some surprises that make it an unbelievable deal.The build quality of the laptop is SURPRISINGLY GOOD. The top case is still made of plastic, but it feels like a sturdy, durable plastic. The lid of the laptop is actually made out of metal and feels extremely durable. The trackpad on the laptop is actually usable and supports multi-gesture functions. If you\'re coming from a MacBook, you will feel right at home--it\'s not as a good as a MacBook trackpad (those are still king) but this one works very well.The performance of this laptop also blew me away. In real-world tests I would say that this is about as powerful as my 2015 MacBook Pro (they have similar hardware components). It handles Photoshop, Illustrator, and Premiere Pro like a champ.My absolute favorite thing about this laptop though, is that it has TWO internal drive bays: an m.2 slot AND a 2.5-inch SATA port, so when I got this laptop I removed the included 128GB SSD, and put in my own 1TB m.2 SSD AND a 1TB 2.5-inch SSD. Also, while this laptop has RAM soldered to the board, it has a DDR4 expansion slot on the inside so you can expand the memory further. If you were to configure a MacBook Pro from Apple, this same configuration would cost you anywhere from $2500 to $3000!! With this laptop, I spent about $550 total with the SSDs and RAM I added.The only real downside of this laptop is the display. It\'s by no means a BAD display, it\'s extremely capable of doing regular work on, and it\'s very bright. But it\'s a lower-resolution display, so if you\'re doing like Photoshop work or something like that, it can feel a little cramped. The display also does not display colors very accurately, colors are very unsaturated, and it blue-shifts the colors too. So if you\'re doing important graphical work, this laptop screen is not that great, but for everyday tasks it will do just fine.The other downside is battery life, it\'s nowhere near as good as MacBook battery life, but it\'ll hold out for an hour or two without being plugged in.But yeah, if you just need a laptop for getting on the internet, Facebook, watching YouTube, this laptop is great. Far more capable than a tablet, it\'s got a nice big 15-inch display, has a keyboard, it\'s real fast, if you need more storage you can add it later. I would absolutely recommend this laptop for everyday folks.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.459,1,'2020-07-31 01:00:46.942819'),(108,182,'AEHI4M2GBJ5JDSZEOV7XGM4YQW7A','M','the United States','January 10, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEHI4M2GBJ5JDSZEOV7XGM4YQW7A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I bought this laptop for my girlfriend who doesn\'t need to do more than simple tasks. I am an engineer so my standards are pretty high but this laptop really impressed me. The SSD was very fast so Windows will start up in just a few seconds. The laptop comes in Windows \"S\" mode which is more secure but only allows you to download applications from the Microsoft store. I ended up turning this off which was very easy but I think that\'s a great feature for a lot of people. The laptop also felt durable.I can\'t speak much to the battery life as I only set it up for her but it seemed pretty good. My only minor complaint about it is the screen quality seemed pretty cheap. There can be a lot of glare, not much contrast, and you can see blocks of pixels, but for the price range, I didn\'t expect much. I\'m very happy with this purchase.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.837,1,'2020-07-31 01:00:46.948802'),(109,254,'AF3QQNCGXSZJHTZV64DEN3WKUHLA','Flo471066','the United States','January 6, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AF3QQNCGXSZJHTZV64DEN3WKUHLA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Great PC! Really fast, light and has a long battery life. I thought the smaller  screen size may be an issue, but it is actually great - goes from edge to edge. Does the job very well. The only slight down side (and thus 4 star rating) is that the mouse pad pivot mechanism isn\'t too good. It is very insensitive to the \"click balance\" so is slow/hard-work and not very responsive. You have to really hard click each side of the pad to cut, copy, paste etc....This is a purely mechanical issue. Given all the other up sides to this great little machine, its something to tolerate...but it gets quite frustrating at times.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.677,1,'2020-07-31 01:05:04.146821'),(110,254,'AFNZC2RMAEA2KOM4U4QZUFOPIVXA','Rob MacGregor','the United States','November 20, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFNZC2RMAEA2KOM4U4QZUFOPIVXA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This is a beast.  IT is my new go to travel laptop.  Plenty of horsepower to run anything I throw at it including some older games.Quality build and well worth the money.  I love this device.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.675,1,'2020-07-31 01:05:04.151807'),(111,261,'AHCPM3YET7ZQOVGQLX2IU3HZXSXA','jay gee','the United States','July 25, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHCPM3YET7ZQOVGQLX2IU3HZXSXA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  its a laptop\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.6,0.958,'2020-07-31 01:05:41.078858'),(112,281,'AHPOYXXNYEHKID3X7QZOUHGSFA7Q','Eric ','the United States','October 14, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHPOYXXNYEHKID3X7QZOUHGSFA7Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Love this computer so far. It is super lightweight and easy to carry anywhere while at the same time the screen is quite large and high quality. The facial scanner is very convenient and the screen pad is pretty nifty too. That is the reason I paid $50 extra for this laptop as opposed to the previous years model.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.757,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.785174'),(113,281,'AEKVASQDGFIZGJVCSGNTKNSSMPOQ','Larry AZ','the United States','December 30, 2019',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEKVASQDGFIZGJVCSGNTKNSSMPOQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Shortly after I received the laptop (and before I had fully grasped hoe to use the screen touchpad) the major Windows 10 update was installed. The touchpad stopped responding, the F6 key to toggle the touchpad on/off quit working. The Bluetooth mouse I had connected stopped working too. After several days of frustration (I was ready to return it) every time I restarted the laptop it notified that software and/or drivers were being updated. First the Bluetooth mouse began working, later the touchpad began to respond, and finally the F6 key responded correctly. It appears that the advanced features of the Vivobook were not available in the Windows 10 \"update\" and that Asus drivers had to catch up. A month later all malfuncfions seem to be corrected. It is very stylish and thin laptop. I am glad I kept it!!!!\n\n','negative','subjective',0.754,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.791157'),(114,281,'AF37TRM7JARZ5VMBKW25XQZS66ZQ','Eug','the United States','November 1, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AF37TRM7JARZ5VMBKW25XQZS66ZQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Very satisfied with the purchase so far.  I\'ve been eyeing the Vivobook line for quite some time and certainly glad I pulled the trigger on this.  You get a sleek machine with impressive specs that feels very high-end, at a very attractive price.  Love the Facial Recognition feature which makes for a quick login.  Haven\'t quite figured out how to incorporate the Screenpad 2.0 into daily use, but it\'s fun to have.  The only gripe I have is on the sound where seems a bit weak/stereo-like - but I guess that\'s standard for slim laptops these days.  Something that can be fixed with a bluetooth headset, speakers, soundbar.  I highly recommend this good value buy.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.543,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.796144'),(115,281,'AED2VOGRE6L6RVXNF6OJGOMF3JPQ','enyerbert uzcategui','the United States','July 19, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AED2VOGRE6L6RVXNF6OJGOMF3JPQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Excelente priducto, tal como se describe\n\n','negative','unknown',0.609,0,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.801131'),(116,281,'AF3FC2M7X5WBWNG5R66ZJN6AALXQ','Amazon Customer','the United States','December 4, 2019',2,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AF3FC2M7X5WBWNG5R66ZJN6AALXQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I really wanted to keep this laptop, it\'s lightweight, not as fast as my other laptop, but fast enough. Fans us a bit loud, but the mini screen was so cool, extending and duplicating my screen was amazing! Unfortunately, as soon as I tried to switch duplicate screen with the switch button, the screen turned black and never worked again. Mind you, this was day one :(. Unfortunately,  I had to return it, maybe it will take a bit longer before this technology is perfect, but I can\'t wait till it is, I am a dev, so I am excited for when they finally release their SDK for the screenpad.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.921,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.807115'),(117,281,'AFHTAFTML4FQJU4NGHIURLPOHICA','Rebecca Deane','the United States','June 12, 2020',1,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFHTAFTML4FQJU4NGHIURLPOHICA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  WI-FI Driver did not work out of the box when setting up, so couldn\'t connect to Internet. Had the warranty and spoke with tech support and they tried to help me fix it, but it didn\'t work. So had to send it back the day I got it.  And if I wanted to replace it directly the price now for ordering a replacement is a hundred dollars more on this model. Guess I\'ll be ordering something else.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.962,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.814097'),(118,281,'AH75IFAZB255VMYFSLTC2ZGG6PSQ','Amazon Customer','the United States','June 5, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AH75IFAZB255VMYFSLTC2ZGG6PSQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Beautiful fast laptop. I will admit that they sent me a teal model when I ordered red, but I’m keeping this one. (Fate works in mysterious ways - I regretted not getting the teal after ordering the red in the first place.)Other than that, the screen is bright and brilliantly colorful, more like my 10th gen iPad than any laptop I’ve ever had. I haven’t had much time to use it yet, but it’s a sleek, beautiful machine.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.554,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.820081'),(119,281,'AF4RD3TZTGTRFBP7BMAVNJSRT7CA','Amazon Customer','the United States','July 12, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AF4RD3TZTGTRFBP7BMAVNJSRT7CA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Bought this laptop a few months ago for telework purposes and am a bit disappointed by the battery life. I find myself having to recharge every 4-5 hours. The mouse trackpad is also extremely sensitive and \"fussy\" at times. I would recommend connecting a bluetooth or usb mouse. If you\'re using it for low intensity uses (browsing, microsoft office, streaming) it\'s a decent laptop.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.997,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:15.825067'),(120,282,'AFYOBU64QIUR2TL62R5J53NKKIQA','David Wellman','the United States','September 15, 2018',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFYOBU64QIUR2TL62R5J53NKKIQA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  UPDATE (04/2019)Rating increased form 3 to 4 stars.As of February 2019, AMD now fully supports Ryzen U with the latest Adrenaline suite. Performance improvements across the board.  In the interim, I\'ve experimented with perhaps exceeding the DDR 2400 memory speed constraint, and despite a setting in the DDR4 sub menu under Device Settings (f12 on POST), memory speed does not exceed 1200 Mhz. Still it is worth it under Windows to increase to 16 or even 32 GB as most modern programs will consume as much memory as is available to them. Still, one last experiment before I declare the F12 menu a placebo: there\'s a setting to change M.2 port from SATA to SATA Express. So, will an NVMe drive work? I actually don\'t have one, but I do intend to at some point and will report success or failure. Finally, despite descriptions to the contrary, Intel AC 9260 WiFi card works just fine. Much better than the Qualcomm that comes standard.So,you may be asking, what is keeping this particular experience from the full 5 stars? I have had issues that, on one occasion, necessitated RMA to Dell (main board died). The fan is now getting quite loud and I do experience intermittent power issues related to wireless card (both the stock AND the Intel replacement) not being able to power on following wake from sleep and adapter warnings (well, it wouldn\'t be Dell without adapter warnings, now would it?)(Original review comments below)Please be aware before purchase AMD does NOT support Ryzen U processors-- directly. More specifically, you will not be able to install the latest Adrenaline driver suite available. That somewhat hampers this machine for media consumption (VLC player does not operate properly) or for light to moderate gaming (sub-optimal frame rates and assorted artifacts). I believe, contrary to what AMD says, those are issues specific to AMD, not Dell. Any Ryzen U based device from any OEM suffers the same lack of updated driver availability.But otherwise, Mrs. Lincoln, how was the play?As such, I can\'t fault Dell too much. The choices for Team Red are few and far between. The Inspiron 13 7375 is a perfectly adequate piece of hardware. Spec-wise, however, it is very much baseline. 8 GB RAM, 256 SSD, and 1080p IPS touch display are the same specifications that my now four-year-old windows tablet has. Speaking of storage, the Micron 1100 M.2 SATA SSD does not feel quite as snappy as a similarly spec\'d Samsung EVO 860 but it’s good enough.  Micron Storage Executive-- providing like functionality as Samsung Magician-- supports this drive and is a strongly recommended install.A lot of the included Dell software is very interesting, and, for the most part, helpful. I\'m particularly curious of Dell Mobile Connect. However, I recommend re-installing Windows from scratch, anyway, and use a standalone backup solution rather than rely on any of the OEM recovery partitions. One can certainly re-install any Dell specific software later.UPDATE 11/2018:Previously, I recommended waiting for the Lenovo Thinkpad A485 to be released before considering AMD Ryzen U based systems. My hypothesis Lenovo was holding off releasing A series until AMD releases a better driver suite to OEMs turned out inconclusive. No significant updates for Ryzen U Vega have existed for almost a year (Still based on Radeon software version 17.7). As of 2018, Nov 23, AMD is blaming OEMs, but AMD won’t even provide reference drivers to general public nor allow Ryzen Master (Overdrive won’t work either)\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.771,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:19.265750'),(121,282,'AGQHEOPURRHIJKF4ELDUT65NYCBQ','Omer H.','the United States','November 11, 2018',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGQHEOPURRHIJKF4ELDUT65NYCBQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  The Ryzen CPU and entire AMD chipset, SSD layout, and \"only 8gb\" of ram, make this infinitely faster than the same with an Intel chip.2-1 capability is sci fi like, perhaps mostly because i only buy a computer every 5-6 years.CONS:NO dedicated PGUP/PGDN/HOME/END buttons - i guess millennial like to scroooolllllll all the time. They\'r not lazy, just inefficient. I should know, i am one of them.Battery life is disappointingly short. With full power, full monitor and full workload, dont expect more than 3 hours.On the upside, at 20% screen brightness and power turned down all the way, this computer is eons faster than anything most people could ever use, and then you get 5-6 hours.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.436,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:19.275799'),(122,282,'AHWNK4X2GRIMDQTZGEAGL7F5QXGA','bchnga','the United States','December 8, 2018',1,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHWNK4X2GRIMDQTZGEAGL7F5QXGA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  The laptop started BSOD after 2 months; unfortunately it is beyond the amazon return policy but still within the Dell warranty. The Indian call center tried to sell me an expansive software warranty before they even bother to look at it. I keep telling them it is a HW problem but they will not acknowledge it. Eventually I ran a few hours of HW stress test myself and fried the wifi card. Replaced it and it now works flawlessly. So it is a HW problem but Dell support thugs will not even investigate.I notice the battery life is not as good as the intel core version of the same model, so stay with that one. I don\'t think the price difference is worth it, plus the casing is also bigger & thicker than the intel equivalent.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.684,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:19.275799'),(123,282,'AG7EON77Q3VSL4BUSFL3JIT4TZ4A','Amazo','the United States','September 2, 2018',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AG7EON77Q3VSL4BUSFL3JIT4TZ4A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Pros:Feels sturdy and durableHas a better GPU than Intel good for game playFacial Recognition (from well lit areas) helps you unlock the computer quicklyType-C USB port for Mirror Display and Charging (Must get a high wattage adapter like the Kamera 80W USB-C Laptop & QC 3.0 Charger separately)Multi-Touch ScreenBack-lit Keyboard settings (Bright, Dim, Off), The four Main Laptop Orientation Modes (Laptop, Tent, Tablet, and Stand) (Not to mention the ability to change the screen\'s orientation from landscape to portrait.)Cons:Long and Several updates needed to be up to date outright (You may experience soft computer crashes otherwise i.e \"Windows 10 didn\'t load properly\". If this happens to you, Do Not Panic. To be fair, if this does happen, he system will boot up again quickly and you will have nothing to worry about except for the updates)Poor Battery Life 3-5 (Maintaining the Laptop properly and Using Power Saver Helps the computer life)720p Camera (Most laptops do come with these types of camera if not worse. For a better quality webcam, you can purchase one such as the Logitech HD Pro Webcam C920 for around $40-$50)Slightly Outdated: Nothing to do with the laptop itself. However By October 2, 2018, Dell is releasing a new line of 2 in 1 Inspirons with more tweaks like a finger print reader, an option to have a 4k display, and an included Dell USB-C charger adapter.Overall: Strongly recommend. Despite a few caveats, this is one of the the best laptops you can get for the price. Even with the newer Dell 2 in 1 laptops. this still holds up pretty well.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.925,1,'2020-07-31 01:08:19.285911'),(124,327,'AFHK3SH7NZ33U6KONJDYYEVM5Q3Q','KrisTK','the United States','May 11, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFHK3SH7NZ33U6KONJDYYEVM5Q3Q','\n\n  I bought this to use with a computer to keep my son from using all the hardcover books in the house to write on and mar the surfaces. It has a nice smooth surface, although it looks textured. Thick enough to not break easily... I could probably stand on it. The rail to support a laptop need to be stuck on with the provided double sided tape to use, which I have not done yet. The large size give enough room to work.\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.474,1,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.232027'),(125,327,'AGULCS5YSAPIIG436K2CSBTCARKQ','Heather C.','the United States','May 27, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGULCS5YSAPIIG436K2CSBTCARKQ','\n\n  I love this mini-desk! With the recent work from home situation, I needed a small desk to sit on my lap. This little desk is so perfect, the bean bag bottom conforms to my lap and creates a level, sturdy workspace.  The bamboo top is smooth and lightweight, my daughter can use it to draw or color. I wish I would have ordered this sooner, it is my favorite new purchase.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.95,1,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.238601'),(126,327,'AG2TH5L6CNR3TOGYZ7JGK3GAFHJQ','Non Hollywood','the United States','December 16, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AG2TH5L6CNR3TOGYZ7JGK3GAFHJQ','\n\n  I work from home a great deal and having a comfortable laptop desk is important.  Love the beanbag comfort.  My dog often sits on my lap underneath it and she loves it too!\n\n','positive','subjective',0.976,1,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.243516'),(127,327,'AFLTWF4BLFEGRRCY4MRZQ5XM6NIQ','CF in Seattle','the United States','November 9, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFLTWF4BLFEGRRCY4MRZQ5XM6NIQ','\n\n  This is the second one I bought as a gift. Very comfortable\n\n','positive','subjective',0.896,1,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.247810'),(128,327,'AHPHHURFFO6GMXMFNZQWYFPRTTCA','Amazon Customer','the United States','May 21, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHPHHURFFO6GMXMFNZQWYFPRTTCA','\n\n  As expected - nice size, comfortable for working on.\n\n','positive','objective',0.759,0.978,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.253505'),(129,327,'AFN3RVIDTMVECSGUWGH3PV2ZFLCA','Caesar ','the United States','May 15, 2019',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFN3RVIDTMVECSGUWGH3PV2ZFLCA','\n\n  I use it to watch video in bed. It angles and sits on the bed on uneven surfaces.\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.596,1,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.258587'),(130,327,'AHG7ZOLC3KVKIIPP4QZDI3GVUUDA','Sarah','the United States','March 21, 2018',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHG7ZOLC3KVKIIPP4QZDI3GVUUDA','\n\n  Very expensive but very comfortable.\n\n','positive','objective',0.602,0.97,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.262873'),(131,327,'AGQAMS26GUFUBZIV6ZER46E46EJQ','Bill R. Helton','the United States','March 10, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGQAMS26GUFUBZIV6ZER46E46EJQ','\n\n  Didn\'t dislike anything about it\n\n','negative','subjective',0.749,1,'2020-07-31 01:14:56.267863'),(132,331,'AFTYWGF5SHO5LPWSSHIP7Y4WFMPA','Nikko','the United States','July 7, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFTYWGF5SHO5LPWSSHIP7Y4WFMPA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  We purchased this laptop knowing its processing speed and spec are not for everyday work.  This laptop is purchased primarily for my Kid\'s online classes during this pandemic.  It does come with everything needed such as a windows license, webcam, and built in speaker.The package is very light, inside there is just the laptop itself and adaptor, plus manuals.  The manual is very simple as there is not much to the laptop.  The webcam on the top has a slider so you can close it when not in a meeting for privacy.  Although lacking num-keys, numbers can be accessed by pressing FN+Numb.  The sound is not the best but it is clear and loud enough for online meetings. I have walked around the house with this laptop and the wifi connection remained stable while windows is downloading update.Setting up windows is painless, clicking through few steps and within 10 minutes you are in windows desktop.  What surprises me is the speed, since built in memory is 64GB and not magnetic, it is reasonably fast at loading windows/app.  Another thing to note is this is vanilla windows they installed, there is absolutely no bloatware like you would get from other brand laptop.  Tested both Edge and Chrome browser for meeting, everything runs like it should out of the box.TL;DL, this is a budget laptop for light browsing, watching videos, and online meetings.  It is lower end spec but functions perfectly smooth.Update : Having accidentally enabled the numb on touchpad and could not reproduce it, I contacted the tech support of Winnovo, they are more than helpful.  They sent me back this instruction in my photo.  To enable numb entry on touchpad, hold your finger at SLIDE (don\'t press down) for 3 seconds, slide it down to an icon that looks like a sheet/numb chart.  To return back to touchpad mode, hold your finger at SLIDE, and slide up to cursor icon.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.877,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:28.939960'),(133,331,'AEARCHDF57H4VVQHDB3HFQHBNXLA','young','the United States','July 6, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEARCHDF57H4VVQHDB3HFQHBNXLA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  The whole is very light and handy, so it is convenient to carry, and you will not feel tired.  The colors are also very comfortable, and no noise or other phenomena occur.  The battery power is sufficient, but the power cord is a little shorter, and it will be better if it is longer.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.905,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:28.946471'),(134,331,'AFWA4OSK6NCWWFBBVYWYDALJVK6A','Patricia Meighan','the United States','July 1, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFWA4OSK6NCWWFBBVYWYDALJVK6A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  sleek, numeric key board, nice camera, and easy set-up\n\n','positive','objective',0.896,0.907,'2020-07-31 12:35:28.952380'),(135,331,'AHIGXT5DOTUT2PLGXMVZA35F5K7A','Amazon Customer','the United States','July 28, 2020',1,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHIGXT5DOTUT2PLGXMVZA35F5K7A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  doesn\'t not accept windows.  when trying to program it keeps turning but you cannot do anything.  runs much slower than my old compoter and I had the geek squad come in two hours and nothing done told me it was a lemon.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.952,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:28.955866'),(136,331,'AG4R5VWJOYXFUDEXDP4WVGEYVSXA','JB','the United States','July 14, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AG4R5VWJOYXFUDEXDP4WVGEYVSXA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Bought this for simple video editing. I wouldn’t highly recommend for anything r a l high tech. It does seem to be a decent quality for the price. Everything seems functional. Took me a minute to adjust but everything seems in order. Would love a more in depth user guide.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.471,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:28.961597'),(137,331,'AG5L34VS3L6BEXMTC45UKCKPAFLQ','crystal anderson','the United States','July 24, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AG5L34VS3L6BEXMTC45UKCKPAFLQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  The price is cheap, but it is efficient and gets the job done.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.387,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:28.966993'),(138,331,'AF3WSOVBU2BXU3BHYXQ7YGWPLHJQ','PernXX','the United States','July 15, 2020',1,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AF3WSOVBU2BXU3BHYXQ7YGWPLHJQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Cheaply made, stops working after the FIRST day of use, seems it is 100% plastic the ports do not work had to get a refund. Do not buy this is not worth the money.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.772,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:28.971852'),(139,332,'AEDFUIC6XTFD356JF47GDQEDKBMA','Nate','the United States','February 19, 2020',3,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEDFUIC6XTFD356JF47GDQEDKBMA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Let me explain what the use case was hete: my partner uses a laptop for writing, grading, internet research, listening to music and the occasional movie, fairly light applications. However, they use it 6-8 hours a day, public transit commute with it, travel with it, and use it at home, so heavy use in that sense. We were hoping that since their requirements were minimal a cheaper laptop would work.Unfortunately, out of the box the thing chugged. Internet explorer had trouble starting. A partially closed screen put the laptop into black screen limbo where it was on but the screen wouldn\'t come back,  forcing a hard restart. It was light, and it ran, but it became clear that every little thing was going to be slow and take a fight. For a machine that was going to used 8 hours a day it wasn\'t going to work.  We returned it and got a cheap surface book instead.Now, that said this is a specific use case. The laptop works (maybe not as well as advertised, certainly not as well as some of the glowing reviews indicated) and it\'s $200. If you don\'t mind it being slow and don\'t need it do much heavy lifting it could work for you.  But that is my review based on this use case, I hope it\'s helpful.\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.602,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:53.626258'),(140,332,'AGPLMZUHO4OAWDJCMIY52PZ3A77Q','B Wesley','the United States','February 3, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGPLMZUHO4OAWDJCMIY52PZ3A77Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I was extremely impressed with how attentive the Support team was, when I contacted them with a question and an issue with my laptop. While this ended up not being the model that fit my lifestyle, they took my product feedback and replied diligently across days.  They also managed to sell me up to the next-higher model, the LapBook Pro, which I have been absolutely thrilled with.A surprisingly impressive 1080P screen, a tiny form factor and solid metal construction make this a great carry-on laptop. The HeroBook Pro doesn\'t have a lot of horsepower and that\'s actually literally why I sought it out. I was looking for low-watt Intel thin\'n\'lights that have power-sipping CPU\'s and not a giant charging brick for a tiny travel bag, without forfeiting screen resolution. The $250 price tag make Chuwi\'s lineup attractive, and the qualtiy metal construction made it a good value, I feel.I would suggest, if you can, looking at the next-up model (the LapBook Pro) for juuuuuust the right amount of power for on-the-go, even for streaming intense 3D games from Steam Link or GeForce Now.But, if you just want to watch downloaded videos or catch up on email, the HeroBook Pro will accomplish all the fundamental tasks.  Its 8GB RAM is enough to happily run Win10. It screen is better than the cheap 768p panels on MOST budget devices. And it isn\'t limited to ChromeOS despite being half the price of many/most prominent branded Chromebooks.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.554,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:53.631663'),(141,332,'AFSJOQATM5Q37NQMZORAUHV3PJ3A','Rosemary','the United States','May 12, 2020',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFSJOQATM5Q37NQMZORAUHV3PJ3A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  So this is with the laptop here for ~24 hours.1. it arrived sooner than expected.  I ordered it 5/2 and it arrived 5/10 -- so about a week quicker than expected.2. The laptop was extremely well packaged.3.  As expected, it\'s quite light (fragile).  I haven\'t weighed to compare, but it\'s comparable to my older ipad in its case.  I wouldn\'t recommend this for a machine that you\'re going to be carrying around and opening and working with it in a variety of conditions.  Definitely not milspec grade.4,  I selected this laptop with some firm criteria: cost, 8GB, & SSD.  When I found this, I ran it past my husband who\'s stronger technically than I am.  He looked over the description, read the reviews, and conditionally approved it.  His concerns were that it wasn\'t that fast of a processor, but as I\'m mainly using this for browsing web sites and keeping track of my email, that\'s not a big issue as not a lot of cpu processing is called for.  The fact that it doesn\'t have a fan is a big plus as its quieter and one less mechanical part that could break.  I wish they made one w/a larger screen but the pricing is amazing.  And it is a higher-resolution screen.5. Out of the box, I turned the laptop over to my husband for him to get the initial setup completed.  He got it up and running on our house network, installed security sw and handed it back.  He commented that it was a pretty good little laptop and especially good at the price.  (It\'s quite convenient when you\'re married to your IT guy.)6. So one little (literally) issue has come up.  This afternoon when I went to use the laptop, I noticed the battery power had dropped quite a bit.  Checked the connection to the cpu and outlet. All good but still running down.  Got my husband involved later this afternoon.  He went and got some meter and there was a question about if the problem was the power source or the port it plugs into.  Much fiddling around.  That\'s when we discovered that we had the power plugged into the headphone jack.Okay fine.  Most  cpus have a different-sized jack, probably for that reason.  Once we got that sorted out, it went back to charging.  With the laptop open and facing you so that you can view the screen, it plugs in on the left.  Oh, and the battery icon shows a wee tiny plug next to the battery.  I told my husband/IT guy that he lost some cred on this issue.I may come back and add more comments as I continue to use this laptop.  My original reaction is that this is a fairly fragile laptop.  I wouldn\'t recommend it for people who want to haul it around to meetings or buy one for people/kids who want to use it for gaming or while working on the bus or at the beach.  On the other hand, it\'s a darn good cpu for the price.I am a happyish camper.So, still\n\n','positive','subjective',0.475,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:53.636165'),(142,332,'AEPUGOZNSHQONCBDK26F2AN2CMDA','Musical_Llama','the United States','April 25, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEPUGOZNSHQONCBDK26F2AN2CMDA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This thing is a heck of a deal for what you get.  8G RAM, a decent sized SSD, IPS FHD screen.  Yes, it\'s made of plastic but it feels pretty good.  It\'s fanless.  The screen is excellent.  Running Ubuntu 18.04 with no problems (make sure you get the realtek audio driver from the current source).  5.4 kernel.  They keyboard is fairly good after you get used to it.  The touchpad is large and is very easy to use, no problems or jumpiness.  The Celeron N4000 is a bit pokey but if you keep your overhead down, it\'s very useable and the fanless aspect of it is really nice.  I hope they make a few more models of these.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.71,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:53.641845'),(143,332,'AFTNJJKUBAG5TV3HXMLJVF3Y6KKA','Lisa Wainright','the United States','February 16, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFTNJJKUBAG5TV3HXMLJVF3Y6KKA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This computer has served it\'s purpose well to date. If you are in need of a lightweight computer with good battery life and decent memory (for the price you can\'t complain), then this is the laptop for you. The build feels cheap.. but does not disappoint me. The processor is weak, but if you are buying this computer for CPU intensive tasks then maybe you should read and understand the description of the pc before you purchase it.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.374,1,'2020-07-31 12:35:53.646734'),(144,332,'AHXEHVB4LT5CNUZ74PX2TA3EKBGA','Mario González Torrecillas','the United States','February 3, 2020',3,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHXEHVB4LT5CNUZ74PX2TA3EKBGA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  -Funciona bien para actividades básicas (ofimática, navegar en internet, etc).-La batería no es tan buena, a mí me da 3-4 horas de pantalla utilizandola de manera regulrar (espero mejore con el tiempo con los ciclos de carga)-Tarda demasiado en cargar completamente (4 a 5 horas de 0 a100%)\n\n','positive','unknown',0.579,0,'2020-07-31 12:35:53.651422'),(145,348,'AFFVX2L2S2CVQU5YPEGAYHZSUYRA','Kingsman','the United States','June 7, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFFVX2L2S2CVQU5YPEGAYHZSUYRA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Best bang-for-your-buck Chromebook, with the beauty of a high-end yet overly priced Samsung, Asus, or Pixelbook. This little book is perfect in almost every way.In general, this Chromebook is perfect for what I bought it for: work-related tasks on the web, surfing the web, using Google Docs to type up documents & write lyrics for songs, and organizing thoughts and ideas into productivity apps and jotting down tasks in my Microsoft To-Do list app.  This Chromebook is lightning fast in powering up, connecting to WiFi & Bluetooth, and opening apps & browsers.The Screen size is non-jeopardizing; large enough for a functional workspace, but small enough to easily store away in a backpack. Bezels are a lot smaller than most budget Chromebooks; I honestly prefer a little bezel to grab the screen without the mouse thinking you\'re trying to press something.The keyboard is unbelievable. Typing is extremely fast and responsive. Perfectly spaced keys. It\'s quiet, and has just the right amount of click so you know when you typed a letter. It\'s back-lit, but dims off when not in use. You will have to change the search key to caps lock in the settings, if that is something you\'re used to.The mouse is very responsive as well. I have purchased a Logitech Pebble in black which matches perfectly; it also pairs up via Bluetooth, so you don\'t have to have a USB receiver sticking out of the side of your Chromebook!The battery life so far is all-day. I think we all know how nice it is to open a Chromebook/Laptop and still have most of the juice in it. One of my favorite things about Chromebooks, including this one, is having a USB-C charging port on EITHER side of the device; therefore, if there is an outlet closer to you on one side, you can connect to that side.The price is unreal; $409 for a 10th gen i3, this thing is just as fast if not faster than older gen i5 and i7 computers. RAM hasn\'t been an issue, nor 64 GB memory. I store all of my documents on Google Drive, so storage is not an issue. Additionally, there is a microSD port on the side, but I decided not to use it since the SD card isn\'t completely flush.Last BUT NOT LEAST, this thing is sleek and elegant. This is THE nicest looking Chrombook in the low-budget range. The charcoal/dark grey is beautiful and modern. The keys, hinges, screen, and logos are minimal and pleasing. The use of space is perfect; the speakers are on either side of the keyboard. No space is wasted in this Chromebook. The screen has a nice glossy shimmer.There is only ONE con to this amazing machine, and it is a minor one: opening the screen. Unlike the Pixelbook Go, this Chromebook takes two hands to open. There no cut-out on the screen lid, so it can sometimes be tricky to open, especially since the device is very thin. Like I said, this is not only minor, but it is the ONLY issue I have come across.Overall, I can hands down recommend this device over all other Chromebooks. This is THE ONE.  Affordable, practical, and exquisite. Well done Lenovo. Thank you for saving me money in a time like this.\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.56,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:33.794821'),(146,348,'AEJQO2DEVMECTIHN7YL473KEWIDA','Shige-san','the United States','June 2, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEJQO2DEVMECTIHN7YL473KEWIDA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  With our kids needing more time on computer for their schoolwork during the COVID19, we finally decided to purchase a chromebook.  What I wanted was a unit with 14\" monitor, FHD, at least 4GB Ram, at least 64GB storage, a decent processor, and touchscreen.  That got my attention on Asus Flip 434 and HP X360 but perhaps due to the dwindling inventories, I was not finding any attractive deals for these or any of the mid range chromebooks in the weeks studying the market.And then I came across the soon to be released Lenovo Chromebook Flex 5 with all but one of the spec I was looking for; it has a 13.3\" monitor.  But at $409, I could deal with the slightly less monitor size so I preordered a unit.The product came 1 day early and we had it for close to a week now.  The build quality is solid with quality feel throughout. One exception is the edge along the trackpad at the very side of the unit.  When flipping the laptop to a tablet, I noticed the edge plastic along the trackpad move slightly since it is thin. We\'ll see if it can withstand the usage by our kids.  But that is the only concern I have.The display is very crisp with wide viewing angle.  I like the keystrokes on the keyboard.  It zips through any of the activities we do granted we are using mostly for web browsing and video conferencing. The only game my kids tried was Roblox since their 3 year old tablet is having hard time playing it.  The Flex 5 plays it very smoothly.For me, this is my first Chromebook experience so I\'m still getting used to the little differences from the PC/Windows but it\'s not that difficult.  It\'s no different then when a new version Windows is released.I am very pleased with the purchase and hope one unit will be enough for the four of us：）\n\n','negative','subjective',0.595,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:33.801799'),(147,348,'AGCVJS3O73FAHCXHUD2XKZIS2EHA','Dean','the United States','June 4, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGCVJS3O73FAHCXHUD2XKZIS2EHA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I have used Chromebooks from day one. I have had different ones from the cheapest to top of the line. I gave my  Pixelbook GO to my mother and intended to get another one. Then I saw this one and had to try it. This is hands down one of the best Chromebooks I have ever used. The screen is great, keyboard and track-pad are superb. The up facing speaker are load and clear. Love that it has both a full size USB port and a sdcard slot. It has no problems running any app I use plus any Linux programs I use daily. All this at half the price of a Pixelbook. If you are looking for a Chromebook, you cant go wrong with this unit. I am overly pleased.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.379,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:33.806337'),(148,348,'AG4OCI27643A75VMLKVY5TBOD63Q','Ivan','the United States','June 6, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AG4OCI27643A75VMLKVY5TBOD63Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  I\'ve used quite a few Chromebooks before (Samsung, Pixelbook, Acer, HP). This time I wanted something that had a 14\" Full HD screen and an Intel Core i3+ processor (main for my children to use), but also wanted something that was snappy.For $400, this Chromebook has been impressive and has a solid build and is fairly lightweight.- Keyboard is great with keys nicely placed.- The HD touchscreen is sharp- The unit performs well with a moderate amount of tabs open, streaming two Youtube videos is no problem.- The flip screen is a nice touch- There\'s a good # of ports as well (dual USB-C, USB-A, headphone jack, mini-SD card slot)- The webcam is great for video conferencing (even comes with a neat built-in webcam cover ).- Installing apps from the Google Play store was simple enough.It is a great Chromebook this price point!\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.484,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:33.811004'),(149,348,'AHW4INA5V535CWB3DNQ2B6ZH74EA','David O.','the United States','May 27, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHW4INA5V535CWB3DNQ2B6ZH74EA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Just received  it today so it\'s still early. Very impressed so far with the speed and build quality. All around a great value for a solid Chromebook.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.946,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:33.817395'),(150,348,'AGRQNSSPMIMWYTP2MEBB2TRBGI2A','Tim jr','the United States','June 2, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGRQNSSPMIMWYTP2MEBB2TRBGI2A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  What can I say it’s just as good as I thought it would be. It’s well made and very fast! My other laptop that runs windows 10 has a i7, 8GB of ram, and a SSD. This feels just as fast (or faster) for half the price and better portability.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.709,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:33.821318'),(151,346,'AFFVGHILIOAIQZKMHMTWE6UMHNGA','Aron ','the United States','April 15, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFFVGHILIOAIQZKMHMTWE6UMHNGA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  The computer was originally really slow and i had to pay for a program to hard defrag the drives because the free software wasn\'t cutting it. I was originally kinda mad because of this but when Brown-box saw what happened they immediately tried to made it right! I told them i didn\'t want a replacement and sent them my receipt for the program i bought and they refunded me for it! The computer now runs pretty smooth and im happy with it.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.974,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:40.615128'),(152,346,'AGDHID76VJ62OO6H5NIJSJI6KGBQ','michael bland','the United States','May 8, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGDHID76VJ62OO6H5NIJSJI6KGBQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Loaded with everything I needed for i line classes\n\n','neutral','subjective',0.465,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:40.625038'),(153,346,'AFJSCZZ3L4XOTIJ24ABL6IRZGJ6A','Amazon Customer','the United States','May 8, 2020',1,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFJSCZZ3L4XOTIJ24ABL6IRZGJ6A/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Just received this yesterday and it is so insanely slow that I cannot do anything on it, it just keeps crashing. Not sure if there’s something I can download to make this not be like this, but it’s absolutely ridiculous\n\n','negative','subjective',0.856,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:40.630542'),(154,346,'AE357QPCV5WSBTKWFMHBSRGH5A3Q','@iAmShayTierra','the United States','June 21, 2020',2,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AE357QPCV5WSBTKWFMHBSRGH5A3Q/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Slowest laptop I’ve owned since dial up. If I didn’t need it I’d have sent it back. I recovered it once already to make sure it was the laptop and nothing that I downloaded but it’s still slow as ever. Not sure why at all since it’s a TB hdd. Maybe it’s the processor. Either way never again.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.615,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:40.635207'),(155,346,'AHCE3ENYBVTU3AUEUSPKNFKWFVFA','Eliza Bonnett','the United States','June 29, 2020',2,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHCE3ENYBVTU3AUEUSPKNFKWFVFA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This computer is incredibly slow while starting up and loading applications. I installed origin and it gave me error notifications every time I tried to open it for a few hours. Isn’t worth the fuss.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.984,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:40.640604'),(156,346,'AGPXPBAEZVWXEUYCQQFBYPI37SZA','Patricia Porco','the United States','April 30, 2020',2,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGPXPBAEZVWXEUYCQQFBYPI37SZA/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  This is a nice-looking laptop with a crisp picture. However, the Intel i3 processor is slow. And it doesn\'t move seamlessly from one tab to the other. Good luck getting into a business meeting. Once I was able to get in and once I wasn\'t, all within an hour! This is being returned. Speaking of returns, it was sold to me as new but it was had been used. It even had the original owner\'s name, email, and password stored in it, so I had to clean the drive before I could even use it.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.806,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:40.646502'),(157,346,'AEJOSGFKL2236LDP37APRP2PIHFQ','Dan Walter','the United States','July 17, 2020',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEJOSGFKL2236LDP37APRP2PIHFQ/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_gw_tr?ie=UTF8','\n\n  Use mostly for word processing, but it\'s fast and reliable. Great upgrade from the Dell Laptops I had been using. Very satisfied.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.968,1,'2020-07-31 12:37:40.654154'),(158,151,'AFMJBG6WPLAWFIPGG3A45UY7FUIQ','Taylor Murphy','the United States','December 3, 2018',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFMJBG6WPLAWFIPGG3A45UY7FUIQ','\n\n  I got this laptop during the Cyber Monday sale as my first ever computer that doesn\'t have Windows on it. My desktop at home has Windows 10 on it but I haven\'t turned it on yet since this Chromebook arrived last week since I wanted to give the Acer a fair chance and see how much I really miss Windows 10. So far, there hasn\'t been anything that has made me wish I was using Windows 10! The only times where I have felt a little bit inconvenienced is when I need to use Microsoft Office products. I say that I was only slightly inconvenienced because I am still able to use all of the Office programs (in multiple ways actually, now that there is Google Play Store support), they are just a different layout than I am used to and may not have some of the more extensive features that the Windows version has. For the vast majority of users, however, there will be a small adjustment period and then it\'ll be fine after that.To give you an idea of how much I use my laptop, I am a medical student and was worried that I wouldn\'t be able to use the programs that I needed for school (Uworld questions, Anki flashcards, etc) but this is where the Google Play Store really comes in handy. As an android phone user, I am very familiar with the Google Play Store and was happy to see that I could download most of the apps I have on my phone and most of them sync seamlessly (like lecture notes using Squid and the other apps that I mentioned earlier). Having the ability to use it as a tablet with the stylus and palm rejection makes taking notes in lecture significantly easier and they immediately sync to my phone so I can study anywhere. Also, the 3:2 aspect ratio makes using PDF textbooks way easier to read compared to most laptops. Overall, I am very happy with my purchase and impressed with how far ChromeOS has come in such a short period of time. Highly recommend!!Pros:+ Light OS makes boot times <5 seconds and efficient use of space, as well as great battery life.+ Screen looks great and gets plenty bright, I usually don\'t go higher than 70%.+ Keyboard is easy to type on and comfortable, also has a backlight which comes in handy.+ Aluminum chassis makes it feel as high quality as it performs, similar look/feel to a MacBook Pro.+ The touchpad is smooth and very easy to use, especially with the added gestures unique to ChromeOS.+ Google Play Store adds a ton of uses/features and allows you to sync apps from your phone easily.+ The foldable touchscreen expands its usability for personal, school, or gaming use.+ Love being able to play my mobile games on the larger display.+ Note taking with the stylus is great, there are plenty of apps in the store to try and it is made by Wacom so it has  great pressure sensitivity and palm rejection.Cons:- ChromeOS takes some getting used to when switching from Windows.- The keyboard also has an adjustment period since it has some variations from the classic Windows keyboard, such as:  ~ Caps Lock is replaced with a search key that searches google in a tab (and also your computer for apps, files, etc).  ~ There is no delete key, use Alt + Backspace instead. It was replaced by a lock key to instantly lock the laptop.  ~ The top row of function keys are replaced with browser keys like forward, back, refresh, task switcher (equivalent  to Windows + Tab on the windows keyboards), etc.  ~ Task manager (Ctrl + Shift + Esc on windows) is now accessible using Search + Esc.- A lot of functionality needs an internet connection so it is somewhat limited when there isn\'t wifi. I use the hotspot  on my phone for when I am in a place without Wifi and it works fine so not much of an issue overall.- There is the occasional issue when trying to use apps from Linux or Google Play Store that aren\'t yet optimized for  Chromebooks that can cause the app to crash.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.443,1,'2020-07-31 12:48:51.524658'),(159,151,'AHQBTRV5CQ4MOOQDE6RAMG2UBX7Q','KaliS-Pugilist','the United States','November 30, 2018',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHQBTRV5CQ4MOOQDE6RAMG2UBX7Q','\n\n  I actually purchased the Pixelbook during Black Friday and thought I got great deal.  Then Cyber Monday came and Spin 13 was on sale for the same price ($699), so I bought one thinking I\'ll check it out and decide on either it of the Pixelbook.  Well, I did my comparison and I really dig the Acer.  The Pixelbook is high-quality construction no doubt, slimmer, a little lighter, and \"prettier\".  The Spin 13 is a TANK...it feels solid in the hands and doesn\'t make you feel like your holding a piece of delicate jewelry, like with the Pixelbook.  I am sending my Pixelbook back to Bestbuy and staying with the Spin 13.  The only thing the Pixelbook seems to have better than it is size and the display can get brighter.  But to be honest the brightness of the display didn\'t really matter because I never rock out with the display on the highest setting anyway.  So at a normal setting for me, about 50%, the screen is just fine.  Putting on max brightness is too much on either laptop.  Also, yes the Pixelbook is lighter.  But it\'s not that much lighter surprisingly.  I was thinking it would really be much lighter and it\'s really not that big of a trade off.  I really hope that Dbrand comes out with some skins for it, that will set the Spin 13 over the top.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.908,1,'2020-07-31 12:48:51.531888'),(160,151,'AHBVC6N645JLF3J64UQA4JV725EQ','blfsmomanddad','the United States','December 3, 2018',5,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHBVC6N645JLF3J64UQA4JV725EQ','\n\n  While I can\'t say how good of a purchase this is at the full price, I bought this while it was on sale for $700 and I could not recommend this Chromebook more.Pros:-Powerful i5-8250U with 8GB of RAM leading to a zero slowdown experience-3:2 aspect ratio giving tons of screen space-Android App and Linux (Crostini) support so you can run practically any application you want-2 in 1 with a pen built in.Cons:-When doing intensive things such as Linux gaming, the fan becomes very loud very quickly and will jump around between different speeds.In-detail explanation:This laptop features an i5-8250U, a processor with 4 cores/8 threads, with maximum turbo boost to 3.4GHz. This gives the laptop metric tons of processing power, and leads to an experience where slowdowns simply do not occur. It uses a screen with a 3:2 aspect ratio. Although some may find this bad as it departs from the standard 16:9 aspect ratio, I personally prefer it as it gives additional screen space. It has Android App support and Linux program support so you can write code or run full Linux desktop applications while also using apps from the giant collection of apps in the Play Store. It also comes with a pen that\'s built in to the bottom right of the laptop and it\'s a 2 in 1 so you can use the laptop as both a laptop and a tablet. However, under intense gaming conditions, the laptop fans become very loud and change volumes rapidly. It also weighs on the heavier side however I wouldn\'t consider that a major downside.\n\n','negative','subjective',0.44,1,'2020-07-31 12:48:51.537205'),(161,151,'AGNZZYYYW6AMURAVMJDNVMUVGPVQ','L. K.','the United States','December 4, 2018',4,'/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGNZZYYYW6AMURAVMJDNVMUVGPVQ','\n\n  Purchased this on Cyber Monday. I previously had an HP Chromebook 14 and wanted another Chromebook. The screen is really nice, but has pretty big bezels (this empty space is similarly noticeable above the keyboard). Overall, just a bit bigger/heavier than you\'d expect a 13.5in laptop to be. Speakers sound pretty good, but they are on the bottom so they get distorted sometimes. Battery is pretty good so far. Performance is quick, but the fan on the bottom can get kinda noisy sometimes when doing something that isn\'t just basic browsing. I was playing a game (Helix Jump) and it at times was laggy, but performance was largely solid. Keyboard is good, but the weird bright spots when the backlit keyboard lights are on are definitely noticeable---though I don\'t really mind them. Stylus is kinda neat, however can ONLY be removed from a specific angle (tablet mode-ish) so be careful when trying to remove it. The lip to actually lift the screen off of the keyboard is extremely small and definitely tricky at times to open. Hope this provides a more informed purchase.\n\n','positive','subjective',0.507,1,'2020-07-31 12:48:51.541842');
